                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="67373" author="pjones" created="Tue, 24 Sep 2013 15:32:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Landed for 2.5.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="66583" author="yujian" created="Fri, 13 Sep 2013 13:23:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch for Lustre master branch: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/7644&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/7644&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hi Chris,&lt;br/&gt;
Could you please improve autotest to install &quot;arm-gp2x-linux-glibc&quot;, &quot;byacc&quot; and &quot;posix&quot; packages by default while provisioning FC18 node? Thanks.&lt;br/&gt;
I just created TEI-574 for this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="66485" author="yujian" created="Thu, 12 Sep 2013 14:03:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can successfully provision FC18 client on Toro now and will create a patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="65053" author="yujian" created="Mon, 26 Aug 2013 08:40:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just found that only arm-gp2x-linux-glibc-2.3.6-11.fc18.noarch.rpm on FC18 contains the header files required by compiling the POSIX test suite. I still need provision an FC18 test node to see whether the header files work or not. However, there is no free Toro test node and provisioning FC18 client node failed on Rosso cluster (TT-1700).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="64971" author="green" created="Fri, 23 Aug 2013 16:56:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;it could be that Fedora does not ship this header too&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="64949" author="yujian" created="Fri, 23 Aug 2013 13:54:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The real failure is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;userintf.c:592:25: fatal error: sys/stropts.h: No such file or directory
compilation terminated.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I need provision an FC18 test node to see which package contains sys/stropts.h, and then ask TT team to install that package while provisioning FC18 test node.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="64369" author="sarah" created="Thu, 15 Aug 2013 22:07:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;lustre-master tag-2.4.90 FC18 also has this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/9b8e3848-056b-11e3-b7d1-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/9b8e3848-056b-11e3-b7d1-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="63968" author="yujian" created="Fri, 9 Aug 2013 14:51:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is blocking the posix compliance testing on FC18 client:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/4b60e11a-fcc2-11e2-9fdb-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/4b60e11a-fcc2-11e2-9fdb-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/655bbc40-cd86-11e2-a1e0-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/655bbc40-cd86-11e2-a1e0-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/4eb3947c-c985-11e2-8cff-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/4eb3947c-c985-11e2-8cff-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
